The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Birla Sun Life Insurance is offering PrimeLife Single Premium plan. It has a minimum and maximum entry age of 30 days and 65 years, while the maturity age is up to 100 years. The minimum premium amount is Rs 20,000 and the face amount is 150 per cent of the amount. It offers a choice of six investment fund options with the flexibility to switch between funds twice a year without any cost. It also offers guaranteed addition in the form of additional units credited at the end of tenth policy year and every five years thereafter.

 Principal Mutual Fund has unveiled a large cap fund, which would mostly invest in stocks with a market capitalisation equal to or greater than Rs 3,500 crore. The fund would charge an entry load of 2.25 per cent for investments below Rs 3 crore and an exit load of 0.50 per cent on investments of Rs 3 crore to Rs 5 crore, if redeemed within three months of investment. The offer is open till October 13.

 UTI-GSF-Brand Value Fund has declared a 45 per cent dividend, the record date being October 10. Birla Equity Plan has declared a dividend of 40 per cent with the record date October 21. It has further declared two more dividend record dates, December 16 and February 17.




